{"id":"1610.00618","submitter":"C\\'esar Lozano Huerta","authors":"Cesar Lozano Huerta","title":"Curvas algebraicas y la pregunta de Halphen","comments":"12 pages, in Spanish, 4 figues. To be published by Miscel\\'anea\n  Matem\\'atica de la SMM","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.HO math.AG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This is an expository paper written in Spanish. This paper discusses the\nanswer and ideas around the Halphen question: what are the pairs (g,d) that\noccur as the genus and degree of a smooth algebraic curve in projective\n3-space.\n  Halphen's question has been studied by many authors, including Halphen in\n1881, Castelnuovo in 1890, and was finally answered almost 100 years later by\nGruson and Peskin in 1981. We (very briefly) sketch arguments by Castelnuovo in\nstudying this question and comment on the ideas of the final answer provided by\nGruson and Peskin. This paper is meant to be brief and elementary introduction\nto some ideas about algebraic curves embedded in projective space and as such,\nwe start out with basic definitions such as that of an algebraic curve, genus\nand degree. Towards the end, we mention some modern developments about this\nquestion as well as directions of research.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Sep 2016 12:47:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-04"}
